# Getting Started

PolicyStack is the archived home of the **policy-federation** package, the
runtime that materialises a single, harness-shaped effective policy out of a
tree of declarative policy fragments. The active development line lives in
[phenotype-tooling](https://github.com/KooshaPari/phenotype-tooling/tree/main/crates/policystack);
this repository retains the Python implementation, CLI, schemas, and tests so
existing deployments keep working.

## What the stack does

Given a project root, a target harness, and a task domain, PolicyStack:

1. Discovers policy fragments under `policies/` (`system/`, `user/`,
   `repo/`, `harness/`, `task-domain/`, plus `suggestions/`).
2. Resolves inheritance, precedence, and risk-tier heuristics via
   `resolve.py` at the repo root.
3. Emits a single effective policy JSON that downstream harnesses consume.

The federated model means a single repo can carry policies for several AI
harnesses (e.g. `codex`, `claude`, `gemini`) without duplicating rules.

## At a glance

| Component        | Path                | Purpose                                    |
| ---------------- | ------------------- | ------------------------------------------ |
| Resolver (CLI)   | `resolve.py`        | Discovers and merges policy fragments.     |
| Python package   | `cli/`              | `policy_federation` importable module.     |
| Schemas          | `schemas/`          | JSON Schemas for fragments and manifests.  |
| Policy sources   | `policies/`         | The actual rules, per harness/domain.      |
| Contracts        | `contracts/`        | Acceptance contracts used by tests.        |
| Wrapper          | `wrappers/go/`      | Go shim invoked by the Python CLI.         |
| Documentation    | `docs/`             | This VitePress site.                       |

## Quick start

The canonical resolution invocation lives in the top-level `README.md`:

```bash
uv run python resolve.py \
  --root . \
  --harness codex \
  --task-domain deployment \
  --emit /tmp/effective-policy.json
```

Requirements:

- Python 3.10 or newer (3.12 is what CI runs against).
- [`uv`](https://github.com/astral-sh/uv) for reproducible script execution,
  or a virtualenv with `policy_federation` editable-installed.
- The Go wrapper is built from source on the CI runner so cross-platform
  binaries work; locally, `go build -o wrappers/go/policy-wrapper ./wrappers/go`
  produces a host-compatible binary.

## Build the docs locally

The docs site is a standard VitePress project rooted at `docs/`:

```bash
npm install --legacy-peer-deps
npm run docs:dev      # live-reload local preview
npm run docs:build    # static build -> docs/.vitepress-dist
npm run docs:preview  # serve the built output
```

`docs:check` runs the build plus the full unit, component, and Playwright
end-to-end test suites; it is the gate the CI workflow uses before publishing.

## Project layout (top level)

```
.
├── ADR.md                # Architecture Decision Records
├── ARCHITECTURE.md       # Cross-cutting design overview
├── CHARTER.md            # Project charter and scope
├── SPEC.md               # Normative specification
├── README.md             # Quickstart + migration notice
├── cli/                  # Python package source
├── contracts/            # Acceptance contracts
├── docs/                 # This VitePress site
├── policies/             # Declarative policy fragments
├── resolve.py            # Resolver entry point
├── schemas/              # JSON Schemas
├── specs/                # Behavioural specs
├── tests/                # Pytest suite
└── wrappers/             # Go wrapper + polyglot shims
```

## Quality gates

PolicyStack enforces several local gates before any change can land:

- **Python:** `ruff check .`, `ruff format --check .`, `pytest`.
- **Go:** `go vet ./...`, `go build ./...`.
- **Docs:** `npm run docs:check`.
- **Git hooks:** `lefthook run pre-commit` and `lefthook run pre-push`.

Run them locally before pushing; the `just grade` (or `task grade`) target
chains every check into a single command.

## Migration notice

This repository is archived. New features and the canonical Rust
implementation now live at
[`phenotype-tooling/crates/policystack`](https://github.com/KooshaPari/phenotype-tooling/tree/main/crates/policystack).
Bug fixes for the Python resolver continue to be accepted here on a
best-effort basis.